 Abdullahi Dikko Former Comptroller-General of Nigerian Customs Service (NCS) Abdullahi Dikko is dead. Dikko was the Comptroller-General of Nigerian Customs Service (NCS) between August 2009 and August 2015. He left office after President Muhammadu Buhari assumed office. A member of the Association of the Nigerian Licensed Customs Agents (ANLCA), who does not want to be named, confirmed the incident to The Nation. Abdullahi joined the Customs in 1988. He was born on 11 May 1960 in Musawa town, a Local Government in Katsina State.